# Testing Conventions

## Fixtures

- `tmp_store` -- isolates filesystem (STORE_DIR, STORE_FILE, REPORTS_DIR) to tmp_path
- `sample_task` -- adds a "test-smoke" task to the isolated store
- `mock_systemctl` -- patches subprocess.run in cursor_schedule.systemd (daemon-reload, enable, disable, start, remove)
- `mock_agent` -- patches shutil.which in cursor_schedule.cli to return a fake cursor-agent path

## Patterns

- Use `click.testing.CliRunner` for CLI tests
- Use `monkeypatch` for store isolation, `unittest.mock.patch` for subprocess mocking
- Mock ALL subprocess.run calls -- never call real systemctl in tests
- `tmp_store` and `mock_systemctl` are independent (no ordering dependency)

## Naming

- Test files: `test_<module>.py`
- Test functions: `test_<behavior>`

## Known Coupling

- `store_sync.py` imports `_read_store` and `_atomic_write` (private API from store.py)
- This is accepted coupling, tracked for promotion to public API in a follow-up
- Tests should mock `cursor_schedule.store_sync.subprocess.run` separately from `cursor_schedule.systemd.subprocess.run`
